(343,28,"top_left_copy","Chinook winds Casino was one of the first major projects I took on when I started working for Gravitate Design Studio, and it is still one of my favorite projects. They had been using Yahoo weather API to display the current weather and 7-day forecast at their beachside casino. Yahoo has since closed its API which resulted in broken functionality for Casino Winds. I had the framework there from the previous developer however because we needed to use a new API service it had to be extensively modified to suit the clients needs. "),
(344,28,"_top_left_copy","field_5cd8ee6c38d5e"),
(345,28,"top_right_photo","30"),
(346,28,"_top_right_photo","field_5cd8ee7b38d5f"),
(347,28,"bottom_left_photo","29"),
(348,28,"_bottom_left_photo","field_5cd8eea638d60"),
(349,28,"bottom_right_copy","My solution was to use 2 different API\'s, one would give me the current weather, and another gave me the forecast. Both of these API\'s had limits on the number of calls that could be made to them per day. Obviously, this would quickly fill up as this is a major casino that has thousands of visitors a day. I was able to work around this by making the call to the API using PHP and saving the data to a JSON file on the server-side. These calls are made once every hour to update the JSON deliver the most up to date weather. Because we are not directly calling on the API every time a customer visits the site we have well below the limits for each API. \r\n\r\nI also had to rebuild the way the weather icons were being synced up. We are using Icomoon for the icons and the use of the new API\'s required an update to the logic that controls which icon to use. This project required the use of all my skills and was a challenge to work on!"),
